<!doctype html>
<html lang="en"><head><meta charset="utf-8"/>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"/>
<title>llm.hostbun.cc — Unified LLM Gateway</title>
<style>
:root{--bg:#0d1117;--card:#161b22;--bd:#30363d;--fg:#e6edf3;--mut:#9aa4b2;--acc:#58a6ff;--grn:#3fb950;--red:#f85149}
*{box-sizing:border-box}
body{margin:0;background:var(--bg);color:var(--fg);font:15px/1.6 -apple-system,Segoe UI,Roboto,sans-serif}
.wrap{max-width:940px;margin:0 auto;padding:32px 20px 80px}
h1{font-size:30px;margin:0 0 4px} h2{margin:40px 0 12px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--bd);padding-bottom:6px}
h3{margin:22px 0 8px}.sub{color:var(--mut);margin:0 0 22px}
a{color:var(--acc);text-decoration:none}a:hover{text-decoration:underline}
code{background:#1f2630;border:1px solid var(--bd);border-radius:5px;padding:1px 6px;font:13px ui-monospace,Menlo,monospace}
pre{background:#010409;border:1px solid var(--bd);border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;overflow:auto}
pre code{background:none;border:none;padding:0}
table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;margin:10px 0}
th,td{border:1px solid var(--bd);padding:8px 10px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top}
th{background:#1f2630;position:sticky;top:0}
.card{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--bd);border-radius:10px;padding:16px 18px;margin:14px 0}
.lane{display:inline-block;font:12px ui-monospace,monospace;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:20px;border:1px solid var(--bd)}
.cloud,.crazyrouter{color:var(--acc);border-color:var(--acc)}.local{color:var(--grn);border-color:var(--grn)}.meta{color:var(--mut)}.claude,.claudecode{color:#d08770;border-color:#d08770}
.warn{background:#2d2212;border:1px solid #9e6a03;border-radius:8px;padding:12px 16px;margin:14px 0}
.danger{background:#2a1416;border:1px solid #7d2b30;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 18px;margin:14px 0}
.danger h3{margin-top:0;color:var(--red)}
.method{font:12px ui-monospace,monospace;color:var(--grn)}
.err{font:12px ui-monospace,monospace;color:#d08770}
#pwrap{max-height:460px;overflow:auto;border:1px solid var(--bd);border-radius:8px}
#pfilter{width:100%;padding:9px 12px;background:#010409;border:1px solid var(--bd);border-radius:8px;color:var(--fg);margin:8px 0;font:14px ui-monospace,monospace}
.num{text-align:right;font:13px ui-monospace,monospace}
ol.flow{padding-left:20px}ol.flow li{margin:6px 0}
summary{cursor:pointer;font-weight:600}
</style></head><body><div class="wrap">

<h1>llm.hostbun.cc</h1>
<p class="sub">One OpenAI-compatible endpoint at <code>https://llm.hostbun.cc/v1</code>. It is the <b>only middleman between any of our code and a model</b>. Three providers, picked automatically from the <b>model id</b>: <span class="lane local">local</span> on-prem GPU (free) · <span class="lane claudecode">claudecode</span> real Claude, billed to your project's pinned Claude Max account · <span class="lane crazyrouter">crazyrouter</span> cloud relay, billed per token. Plus on-prem <b>image generation</b> (<code>model: imagegen</code>). You never send a model key — the gateway injects it. You <b>must</b> send an <code>X-Project</code> header. Docs also at <a href="https://docs.llm.hostbun.cc">docs.llm.hostbun.cc</a>.</p>

<div class="danger">
<h3>Read this before you integrate</h3>
<ul style="margin:0">
<li><b>There is no authentication on <code>/v1</code>.</b> Anyone who can reach this hostname can spend our Claude Max subscriptions and our metered Crazyrouter balance. <b>Treat the URL as a secret.</b> Don't put it in a public repo, a client-side bundle, a Dockerfile you publish, or a screenshot.</li>
<li><b><code>X-Project</code> is attribution, not authentication.</b> It is a self-asserted string. It decides <i>who gets billed</i> and <i>which quota applies</i> — it does not prove who you are, and it stops nobody. Per-project API keys are planned; until they ship, the network boundary is the only boundary.</li>
<li><b>No IP allowlist.</b> Your IP is recorded on every call, but it is never checked. It gates nothing.</li>
<li><b>Every prompt and every reply is stored, in plaintext, indefinitely.</b> See <a href="#data">What gets stored</a>. Do not send secrets, credentials, or personal data you would not put in a shared database.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2 id="how">How it works</h2>
<p>One request, in order. Any step can end it:</p>
<div class="card"><ol class="flow">
<li><b>Project attribution.</b> The gateway reads your project slug (from <code>X-Project</code>, or a body field — see below). No project on an inference call → <span class="err">400 project_required</span>.</li>
<li><b>Routing.</b> The <code>model</code> id picks the provider. <code>local</code>/<code>qwen*</code> → local GPU. Anything starting <code>claude</code> → claudecode. Everything else → crazyrouter. An admin <b>force-model</b>, a per-model <b>override</b>, or a per-project <b>route</b> can redirect this. Unroutable → <span class="err">400 model_not_routable</span>.</li>
<li><b>Usage quota.</b> If your project has a rolling-window limit, usage is summed from the call log. Over the warn threshold → <code>x-usage-warning</code> header. Over the slow threshold → the response is deliberately delayed. Over the hard cap → <span class="err">429 usage_limit_exceeded</span>.</li>
<li><b>Gate</b> (local only). Models listed as <i>gated</i> require <code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;</code>. The normal local model is not gated.</li>
<li><b>Account pinning</b> (claudecode only). Your project is looked up in the pin table. Not pinned → <span class="err">403 no_account_for_project</span>. Pinned → that account's token is injected and the required Anthropic headers are synthesized. <b>Your own <code>Authorization</code> header is overwritten regardless.</b></li>
<li><b>Upstream call.</b> One round trip. On <code>claudecode</code> an OpenAI-shaped body is translated to Anthropic and back; a native <code>/v1/messages</code> body is forwarded byte-for-byte. On <code>crazyrouter</code> and <code>local</code> the body is forwarded as-is with the key swapped.</li>
<li><b>JSON enforcement.</b> If you asked for <code>response_format</code>, the reply is parsed, repaired, or re-prompted before you see it.</li>
<li><b>Logging.</b> The call — including full prompt and full reply — is written to the <code>llmrouter</code> Postgres database.</li>
</ol></div>

<p><b>There is no fallback, anywhere.</b> If the pinned account is out of quota you get its real <code>429</code>. If upstream 500s you get its real <code>5xx</code>. The gateway will never silently answer from a different account or a different provider. That behaviour once hid both the cost and the truth; it is gone on purpose.</p>

<h2 id="projects">For projects — onboarding</h2>
<p>A <b>project</b> is the unit of billing, quota, and blame. It is a lowercase slug (max 64 chars) that names the app making the call — <code>bofrid</code>, <code>promopilot</code>, <code>fb-bot</code>. One project maps to exactly one Claude Max account, forever. Rotating accounts would blow the per-org prompt cache (roughly 12&times; the cost) and make "who spent this?" unanswerable after the fact, so it does not happen.</p>

<h3>1. Pick a slug and always send it</h3>
<p>The gateway takes the project from the <b>first</b> of these it finds, normalised to a lowercase slug:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>X-Project</code> header <i>(preferred)</i> — also accepts <code>X-Consumer</code>, <code>X-Project-Id</code></li>
<li>a top-level <code>"project"</code> field in the JSON body</li>
<li><code>"metadata":{"project":"…"}</code> in the body</li>
<li>the OpenAI <code>"user"</code> field <i>(fallback — handy for SDKs that won't let you set headers)</i></li>
</ul>
<p>Enforcement is <b>on in production</b>. An inference call with no project is rejected:</p>
<pre><code>HTTP 400
{"error":{"message":"missing project attribution: send an 'X-Project' header (or a 'project' body field) identifying the calling app.",
          "type":"invalid_request_error","code":"project_required"}}</code></pre>
<p class="sub">Applies to <code>/v1/chat/completions</code>, <code>/v1/messages</code>, <code>/v1/completions</code>, <code>/v1/responses</code>. It does <b>not</b> apply to <code>/v1/images/generations</code>, <code>/v1/embeddings</code>, <code>/v1/rerank</code>, <code>/v1/audio/*</code>, or any <code>GET</code>.</p>

<h3>2. Get pinned (only if you use <code>claude*</code> models)</h3>
<p><code>local</code> and <code>crazyrouter</code> work the moment you send a project. <span class="lane claudecode">claudecode</span> does not — your project must first be pinned to a Claude Max account by an admin, or every call is refused:</p>
<pre><code>HTTP 403
{"error":{"type":"no_account_for_project",
          "message":"project \"my-app\" is not pinned to a Claude Code account",
          "hint":"pin it in /admin (projectAccounts), or set defaultAccount",
          "pinned_projects":[ … ]}}</code></pre>
<p>The gateway never guesses whose subscription to bill. Ask an admin to add <code>my-app → &lt;account&gt;</code> to <code>projectAccounts</code>. The <code>pinned_projects</code> array in the error body tells you which projects already have one.</p>

<h3>3. Know your quota</h3>
<p>Projects can carry a rolling-window limit (tokens or calls, e.g. <code>24h</code>). Usage is summed live from the call log; nothing is persisted separately. Three thresholds, and the gateway tells you where you are on <b>every</b> response:</p>
<table>
<tr><th>Header</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>x-usage-percent</code></td><td>How far through the window's cap you are, 0–100+</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>x-usage-window</code> · <code>x-usage-limit</code></td><td>The window (<code>24h</code>) and the cap (<code>5,000,000 tok</code>)</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>x-usage-warning</code></td><td>Present past the warn threshold (default 80%). Nothing is slowed yet.</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>x-usage-throttled-ms</code></td><td>Present past the slow threshold (default 95%). <b>Your request was deliberately delayed</b> by this many ms before being forwarded.</td></tr>
</table>
<p>Past the hard cap you get <span class="err">429 usage_limit_exceeded</span> with <code>retry-after: 60</code>, until usage rolls off the window or an admin raises the limit. Limits ship <b>off</b> by default (cap <code>0</code> = unlimited) and are set per-project or per-group in <code>/admin</code>.</p>

<h3>4. Accept that you are being logged</h3>
<p>See <a href="#data">What gets stored</a>. Design your prompts accordingly.</p>

<h2 id="quickstart">Quick start</h2>
<p>One base URL for everything. The <b>model id</b> picks the provider. Same OpenAI API either way. The API key is a placeholder — the gateway injects the real one.</p>
<pre><code># local GPU — free, on-prem
curl https://llm.hostbun.cc/v1/chat/completions -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "X-Project: my-app" \
  -d '{"model":"local","messages":[{"role":"user","content":"hi"}],"max_tokens":512}'

# real Claude — billed to my-app's pinned Max account
curl https://llm.hostbun.cc/v1/chat/completions -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "X-Project: my-app" \
  -d '{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","messages":[{"role":"user","content":"hi"}]}'

# crazyrouter — anything else, billed per token
curl https://llm.hostbun.cc/v1/chat/completions -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "X-Project: my-app" \
  -d '{"model":"gemini-2.5-flash-lite","messages":[{"role":"user","content":"hi"}]}'</code></pre>

<pre><code>from openai import OpenAI

client = OpenAI(
    base_url="https://llm.hostbun.cc/v1",
    api_key="x",                                   # placeholder; gateway injects the real key
    default_headers={"X-Project": "my-app"},       # required on every inference call
)
client.chat.completions.create(model="local",             messages=[{"role":"user","content":"hi"}])
client.chat.completions.create(model="claude-sonnet-4-6", messages=[{"role":"user","content":"hi"}])
client.chat.completions.create(model="gemini-2.5-flash-lite", messages=[{"role":"user","content":"hi"}])</code></pre>

<pre><code>// Node — openai@4
import OpenAI from "openai";
const client = new OpenAI({
  baseURL: "https://llm.hostbun.cc/v1",
  apiKey: "x",
  defaultHeaders: { "X-Project": "my-app" },
});</code></pre>
<p class="sub">If your SDK won't let you set headers, set the OpenAI <code>user</code> field to your project slug instead — the gateway falls back to it.</p>

<h2 id="errors">Error codes</h2>
<p>Every failure is one of these. Nothing is silently swallowed.</p>
<div class="card"><table>
<tr><th>Status</th><th><code>code</code></th><th>Why · what to do</th></tr>
<tr><td class="err">400</td><td><code>project_required</code></td><td>No <code>X-Project</code> on an inference call. Send one.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="err">400</td><td><code>model_not_routable</code></td><td>The model id matched no provider — crazyrouter is <code>off</code> or in <code>allowlist</code> mode and your id isn't on it, or the id is unknown and there's no default route. Fix the id, or ask an admin to allowlist it.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="err">401</td><td><code>unauthorized</code></td><td>You asked for a <b>gated</b> local model without <code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;</code> (or <code>x-api-key</code>). Only applies to specific ids; the normal <code>local</code> model is open.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="err">403</td><td><code>no_account_for_project</code></td><td>Your project isn't pinned to a Claude Max account. <b>Not retryable.</b> Ask an admin to pin it. Body lists the projects that are.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="err">422</td><td><code>json_validation_failed</code></td><td>You asked for JSON, and the model would not produce valid JSON even after re-prompting. Body carries the last raw content.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="err">429</td><td><code>usage_limit_exceeded</code></td><td>Your project hit its rolling-window quota. Honour <code>retry-after</code>, or get the limit raised.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="err">429</td><td><i>(upstream)</i></td><td>The <b>pinned account</b> is out of Claude Max quota, or crazyrouter rate-limited us. This is upstream's real 429, passed through. There is no fallback — waiting is the fix.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="err">5xx</td><td><i>(upstream)</i></td><td>Upstream failed. Passed through verbatim. Retry with backoff.</td></tr>
</table></div>

<h2 id="endpoints">All endpoints</h2>
<div class="card"><table>
<tr><th>Method</th><th>Path</th><th>Provider</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td class="method">POST</td><td><code>/v1/chat/completions</code></td><td>all three</td><td>Chat, routed by <code>model</code>. Streaming, tools, structured outputs, vision, <code>reasoning_effort</code>. <b>Needs <code>X-Project</code>.</b></td></tr>
<tr><td class="method">POST</td><td><code>/v1/messages</code></td><td><span class="lane claudecode">claudecode</span></td><td>Anthropic-native shape, <b>forwarded byte-for-byte</b> — full tool / thinking / prompt-cache fidelity. What Claude Code itself uses. <b>Needs <code>X-Project</code>.</b></td></tr>
<tr><td class="method">POST</td><td><code>/v1/images/generations</code></td><td><span class="lane local">image</span></td><td>Text-to-image on the pbox GPU (SDXL + Lightning). Token injected. No project required.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="method">GET</td><td><code>/v1/templates</code> · <code>/v1/loras</code></td><td><span class="lane local">image</span></td><td>Image templates and named-LoRA catalog</td></tr>
<tr><td class="method">POST</td><td><code>/v1/completions</code> · <code>/v1/embeddings</code> · <code>/v1/audio/*</code> · <code>/v1/rerank</code></td><td><span class="lane crazyrouter">crazyrouter</span></td><td>Rest of the OpenAI-compatible surface, key injected</td></tr>
<tr><td class="method">GET</td><td><code>/v1/models</code></td><td>merged</td><td>What each provider currently advertises — local aliases + <code>claude*</code> ids + crazyrouter's live catalog. This is <b>not</b> the full priced list; see <code>/prices.json</code>.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="method">POST</td><td><code>/local/v1/chat/completions</code></td><td><span class="lane local">local</span></td><td>Legacy explicit local path (still works)</td></tr>
<tr><td class="method">GET</td><td><code>/prices.json</code> · <code>/prices</code></td><td><span class="lane meta">meta</span></td><td>Computed actual prices (discount applied); refreshes every 6h</td></tr>
<tr><td class="method">GET</td><td><code>/dashboard/billing/subscription</code> · <code>/usage</code></td><td><span class="lane meta">meta</span></td><td>Crazyrouter credit limit and usage to date</td></tr>
<tr><td class="method">GET</td><td><code>/docs</code></td><td><span class="lane meta">meta</span></td><td>This page</td></tr>
<tr><td class="method">GET</td><td><code>/admin</code></td><td><span class="lane meta">meta</span></td><td>Admin UI — password-gated. See below.</td></tr>
</table></div>

<h2>Providers</h2>

<h3><span class="lane local">local</span> — on-prem GPU, free</h3>
<p>Select with <code>model: "local"</code> (aliases <code>qwen</code>, <code>qwen3.5-9b</code>). Routes to a <b>llama.cpp</b> server on the pbox RTX 4090. Private — the data stays on-prem. Free. No key. One model, resident on the GPU, no cold start: <b>Qwen3.5-9B</b>, Q4_K_M GGUF, ~5.6&nbsp;GB, 16K context, ~130 tok/s.</p>
<div class="warn"><b>It is a reasoning model, and that will bite you.</b> It emits its chain of thought into <code>reasoning_content</code> and leaves <code>content</code> empty until it finishes thinking. With a small <code>max_tokens</code> it never finishes — you get <code>content: ""</code> and <code>finish_reason: "length"</code>, having paid for every token. Give it <code>max_tokens</code> ≥ 512, or pass <code>"enable_thinking": false</code> to turn thinking off entirely.</div>
<pre><code>curl https://llm.hostbun.cc/v1/chat/completions -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "X-Project: my-app" \
  -d '{"model":"local","enable_thinking":false,
       "messages":[{"role":"user","content":"describe Stockholm"}],"max_tokens":512}'</code></pre>
<pre><code># opencode — opencode.json
{
  "provider": {
    "hostbun-local": {
      "npm": "@ai-sdk/openai-compatible",
      "options": { "baseURL": "https://llm.hostbun.cc/v1", "apiKey": "x",
                   "headers": { "X-Project": "my-app" } },
      "models": { "local": { "name": "Qwen3.5-9B (local)" } }
    }
  }
}</code></pre>
<p class="sub">Legacy ids <code>gemma</code> / <code>obliterated</code> still resolve, but now <b>redirect to Claude</b> — they are not local models any more. The backend that served them is retired.</p>

<h3><span class="lane claudecode">claudecode</span> — real Claude, flat cost</h3>
<p>Any model id starting <code>claude</code> goes to <code>api.anthropic.com</code>, called with the <b>Claude Max account pinned to your project</b>. Cost is flat (a subscription), not per token. Current ids — check <code>GET /v1/models</code>, since Anthropic ships new ones without asking:</p>
<pre><code>claude-opus-4-8   claude-sonnet-5   claude-sonnet-4-6   claude-haiku-4-5   claude-fable-5</code></pre>
<p>Both shapes work: OpenAI <code>/v1/chat/completions</code> (translated on the way out and back) and Anthropic-native <code>/v1/messages</code> (forwarded byte-for-byte). <b>Use the native shape if you care about tool fidelity, extended thinking, or the prompt cache.</b></p>
<p class="sub">The account is chosen <b>server-side, from your project</b>. No request header can change it — not <code>Authorization</code>, not <code>X-Account</code>, not anything. Your <code>Authorization</code> header is discarded and replaced. One project → one account, no rotation, no fallback.</p>
<pre><code># native Anthropic shape — byte-for-byte, keeps the prompt cache
curl https://llm.hostbun.cc/v1/messages -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "X-Project: my-app" \
  -d '{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","max_tokens":1024,
       "messages":[{"role":"user","content":"hi"}]}'</code></pre>

<h3><span class="lane crazyrouter">crazyrouter</span> — cloud relay, <b>billed per token</b></h3>
<p>Every model id that isn't a local alias and doesn't start with <code>claude</code> lands here (upstream <code>crazyrouter.com</code>), key injected. Chat, streaming, tools, structured outputs, vision, embeddings, rerank, image/video/audio generation. <b>This is the only provider that costs real money per request</b> — see the price table below.</p>
<p>An admin can set a <b>crazyrouter policy</b>: <code>open</code> (forward anything), <code>allowlist</code> (only listed ids get through, the rest fall to the default route), or <code>off</code>. If you get <code>400 model_not_routable</code> on a model that clearly exists, this is why.</p>
<pre><code># streaming
curl -N https://llm.hostbun.cc/v1/chat/completions -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "X-Project: my-app" \
  -d '{"model":"gemini-2.5-flash-lite","stream":true,
       "messages":[{"role":"user","content":"count to 5"}]}'</code></pre>

<h2>Structured / JSON output <span class="lane meta">enforced</span></h2>
<p>Send <code>response_format: {"type":"json_object"}</code> (or <code>{"type":"json_schema",…}</code>) on <code>/v1/chat/completions</code> and the gateway <b>verifies the model actually returned valid JSON</b> before handing it back. It does not trust the model to honour the flag. Works identically on all three providers, including models with no native structured-output support.</p>
<ul>
<li>Reply parses as JSON → returned unchanged.</li>
<li>Reply is wrapped in a <code>```json … ```</code> fence → fence stripped, no extra round trip.</li>
<li>Still not valid JSON → the gateway re-prompts the <i>same</i> model with the parse error and retries (default 2).</li>
<li>Model never complies → <span class="err">422 json_validation_failed</span> with the last raw content, instead of a malformed body that explodes your <code>JSON.parse</code>.</li>
</ul>
<p>Anthropic has no <code>response_format</code> field at all. For <span class="lane claudecode">claudecode</span> the gateway <b>strips it and instructs the model in-prompt instead</b> (including your JSON Schema, when given), then validates the same way — so <code>model:"claude-…"</code> with <code>json_schema</code> returns the shape you asked for. <span class="lane crazyrouter">crazyrouter</span> and <span class="lane local">local</span> keep native constrained decoding.</p>
<p class="sub">Because the whole reply must be buffered to validate it, <code>stream:true</code> + a JSON <code>response_format</code> returns the content in a single reconstructed SSE chunk rather than token-by-token. Validation is structural JSON, not full JSON-Schema.</p>
<pre><code>curl https://llm.hostbun.cc/v1/chat/completions -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "X-Project: my-app" \
  -d '{"model":"local","response_format":{"type":"json_object"},"max_tokens":512,
       "messages":[{"role":"user","content":"List 3 primary colors as a JSON array under key colors."}]}'
# → guaranteed-parseable JSON, or HTTP 422 json_validation_failed</code></pre>

<h2>Reasoning effort &amp; extra params <span class="lane meta">passthrough</span></h2>
<p>The gateway rewrites only the <code>model</code> field (and <code>response_format</code>, for JSON enforcement). <b>Every other field is forwarded upstream untouched</b> — <code>reasoning_effort</code>, <code>thinking</code>, <code>temperature</code>, <code>top_p</code>, <code>tools</code>, <code>tool_choice</code>, <code>stop</code>, <code>seed</code>, <code>max_tokens</code>. The gateway sets <b>no default effort</b>; omit the field and the upstream's own default applies. Effort is honoured only where the target model supports it (crazyrouter reasoning models, and Claude on claudecode).</p>
<pre><code>curl https://llm.hostbun.cc/v1/chat/completions -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "X-Project: my-app" \
  -d '{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","reasoning_effort":"high",
       "messages":[{"role":"user","content":"prove sqrt(2) is irrational"}]}'</code></pre>

<h2>Image generation <span class="lane local">model: imagegen</span></h2>
<p>Text-to-image on the <b>pbox RTX 4090</b> (SDXL 1.0 + SDXL-Lightning, ~1.5&nbsp;s for 1024&times;1024), token injected server-side. OpenAI-compatible <code>/v1/images/generations</code>, always returns base64 (<code>{"data":[{"b64_json":…}]}</code>) — we host no URLs. Use <code>model: "imagegen"</code> (<code>"sd-turbo"</code> is a legacy alias). No <code>X-Project</code> required.</p>
<table>
<tr><th>Field</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>prompt</code></td><td>Text prompt. Optional if <code>template</code> is given.</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>template</code></td><td>Named prompt template (<code>GET /v1/templates</code>): <code>profile-woman-back</code>, <code>profile-man-back</code> — profile pics that <b>randomize hair / outfit / scene / lighting</b> per image.</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>vars</code></td><td>Pin specific template slots, e.g. <code>{"hair":"jet black"}</code>; the rest stay random.</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>lora</code></td><td>A <b>registered LoRA name</b> (<code>GET /v1/loras</code>), an HF repo id, or a local path. Stacked on the speed LoRA; the trigger phrase is auto-added to the prompt.</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>lora_scale</code></td><td>Override LoRA strength (default per-LoRA).</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>n</code> · <code>size</code> · <code>seed</code> · <code>steps</code></td><td>Count (1–8), <code>WxH</code> (default <code>1024x1024</code>), seed, steps (default 8).</td></tr>
</table>
<p>Templates return what they picked in <code>data[i].template_vars</code> + <code>data[i].revised_prompt</code>. Named LoRAs currently: <code>watercolor</code> (soft watercolor — good for article headers), <code>nostalgic-cinema</code> (warm film look), <code>hair-bun</code>.</p>
<pre><code>curl https://llm.hostbun.cc/v1/images/generations -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"model":"imagegen","lora":"watercolor","prompt":"a cozy reading nook by a window"}'

# save the first image to a file
curl -s https://llm.hostbun.cc/v1/images/generations -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"model":"imagegen","prompt":"row of colorful Swedish houses"}' \
  | python3 -c "import sys,json,base64;open('out.png','wb').write(base64.b64decode(json.load(sys.stdin)['data'][0]['b64_json']))"</code></pre>

<h2 id="data">What gets stored</h2>
<div class="card">
<p>Every request is written to a <code>calls</code> table in the <code>llmrouter</code> Postgres database. Per call:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Your IP and User-Agent</b>, method, path, timestamp, latency.</li>
<li>Requested model, resolved provider, the model actually sent upstream, which account served it, HTTP status.</li>
<li>Full token accounting — prompt, completion, thinking, <b>cache read and cache write</b>, <code>stop_reason</code>, tool counts, MCP servers used.</li>
<li><b>The full prompt you sent, and the full reply you got back, as plaintext.</b> Uncapped by default.</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Retention is unlimited by default.</b> Rows are never pruned unless a retention count is configured — and even then, <code>claudecode</code> rows are exempt and kept forever. There is no redaction, no scrubbing, no TTL.</p>
<p>Anyone with the <code>/admin</code> password can read every prompt and every reply any project has ever sent, search across them (<code>GET /admin/api/calls?q=…</code> greps prompt and reply text), and export the lot.</p>
<p><b>So: don't send secrets, credentials, tokens, or personal data through this gateway.</b> If you must process sensitive text, use <code>model: "local"</code> — it still gets logged here, but at least it never leaves our hardware.</p>
</div>

<h2>Pricing <span class="lane meta">/prices.json</span></h2>
<p><b>Actual</b> prices for the <span class="lane crazyrouter">crazyrouter</span> provider, per-model discount applied. <span class="lane local">local</span> is <b>$0</b>. <span class="lane claudecode">claudecode</span> is <b>flat</b> — it draws on a Claude Max subscription, not a per-token balance, so it doesn't appear here.</p>
<pre><code>curl https://llm.hostbun.cc/prices.json    # or /prices
# { "generated_at":"…","group_ratio":1,"count":165,
#   "models":[{"model":"gemini-2.5-flash-lite","type":"token",
#              "input_per_1m":0.08,"output_per_1m":0.30,"discount":0.55}, …] }</code></pre>
<p class="sub">Token models: USD per 1M tokens (in/out). Image/video/audio: USD per call. Self-refreshes every 6h — last update: <span id="pgen">…</span>.</p>
<input id="pfilter" placeholder="filter models…  e.g. gemini, gpt-5, glm, embed"/>
<div id="pwrap"><table>
<thead><tr><th>Model (<span id="pcount">…</span>)</th><th>Type</th><th class="num">Input $/1M</th><th class="num">Output $/1M</th><th class="num">Disc</th></tr></thead>
<tbody id="ptbody"><tr><td colspan="5">loading prices…</td></tr></tbody>
</table></div>
<pre><code>curl https://llm.hostbun.cc/dashboard/billing/subscription   # {"hard_limit_usd":13,…}
curl https://llm.hostbun.cc/dashboard/billing/usage          # {"total_usage":…}</code></pre>

<h2>Admin <span class="lane meta">/admin</span></h2>
<p>Password-gated SPA. It is the control plane, and changes apply <b>instantly, with no redeploy</b>, persisting on the volume.</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Routing</b> — force a model globally, override any incoming model to any provider, set the crazyrouter policy (open / allowlist / off), set a default route, trace where a model id resolves, edit local aliases.</li>
<li><b>Keys</b> — swap the Crazyrouter key, toggle the local gate and JSON enforcement. Secrets are masked, never returned in clear.</li>
<li><b>Call log</b> — every request with its full prompt and reply, searchable, plus usage stats broken down by project.</li>
<li><b>Headroom</b> — live 5h / 7d limit utilisation per Claude Max account, harvested for free from Anthropic's response headers. No probe requests.</li>
</ul>
<p class="sub">Programmatic access is the same API the UI uses: <code>POST /admin/api/login</code>, then <code>/admin/api/{state,config,health,models,resolve,test,calls,stats,series,limits}</code>. The <code>claudectl</code> plugin drives exactly these.</p>

<div class="warn" style="margin-top:30px">⚠️ <b>Known gap:</b> the admin UI has no accounts or project-pin panel yet, so a new project can only be pinned by editing the config through the admin API. If you are stuck on <code>403 no_account_for_project</code>, that's why — ask an admin.</div>

<p class="sub" style="margin-top:26px">Node router on hostbun (Coolify) — one URL, model-based routing, zero dependencies. Source: <a href="https://github.com/devdashco/llm-hostbun-router" target="_blank">devdashco/llm-hostbun-router</a>.</p>

<script>
const PRICES='https://llm.hostbun.cc/prices.json';
let ALL=[];
function row(m){
  if(m.type==='token') return '<tr><td><code>'+m.model+'</code></td><td>token</td><td class="num">$'+m.input_per_1m+'</td><td class="num">$'+m.output_per_1m+'</td><td class="num">'+m.discount+'</td></tr>';
  return '<tr><td><code>'+m.model+'</code></td><td>per-call</td><td class="num" colspan="2">$'+m.price_per_call+'/call</td><td class="num">'+m.discount+'</td></tr>';
}
function render(q){
  q=(q||'').toLowerCase();
  const f=ALL.filter(m=>m.model.toLowerCase().indexOf(q)>-1);
  document.getElementById('ptbody').innerHTML=f.length?f.map(row).join(''):'<tr><td colspan=5>no match</td></tr>';
}
fetch(PRICES).then(r=>r.json()).then(d=>{
  ALL=d.models.sort(function(a,b){return (a.input_per_1m!=null?a.input_per_1m:a.price_per_call||0)-(b.input_per_1m!=null?b.input_per_1m:b.price_per_call||0)});
  document.getElementById('pgen').textContent=d.generated_at||'';
  document.getElementById('pcount').textContent=ALL.length;
  render('');
}).catch(function(e){document.getElementById('ptbody').innerHTML='<tr><td colspan=5>failed to load /prices.json: '+e+'</td></tr>'});
document.addEventListener('input',function(e){if(e.target.id==='pfilter')render(e.target.value)});
</script>
</div></body></html>
